+  lines.push(`Resistance and immunotherapy-modifying features were also evident. stk11_mutation was independently adverse (${fmt(term(mainModel, 'stk11_mutation').beta)} months, p=${fmt(term(mainModel, 'stk11_mutation').p)}), and the pembrolizumab-by-stk11 interaction was negative (${fmt(iterations[16].analyses[0].effect_estimate)} months, p=${fmt(iterations[16].analyses[0].p_value)}), supporting attenuated immunotherapy benefit with STK11 alteration. tmb_high was favorable on its own (${fmt(term(mainModel, 'tmb_high').beta)} months, p=${fmt(term(mainModel, 'tmb_high').p)}) and further increased pembrolizumab-associated PFS (${fmt(iterations[18].analyses[0].effect_estimate)} interaction months, p=${fmt(iterations[18].analyses[0].p_value)}).`);
+  lines.push('');
+  lines.push(`General disease-burden and host-status findings were directionally consistent with clinical expectations. Brain metastases were associated with shorter PFS (${fmt(term(mainModel, 'has_brain_mets').beta)} months, p=${fmt(term(mainModel, 'has_brain_mets').p)}), and liver metastases remained adverse after adding metastatic-site indicators (${fmt(iterations[20].analyses[0].effect_estimate)} months, p=${fmt(iterations[20].analyses[0].p_value)}). Higher albumin was favorable (${fmt(term(mainModel, 'albumin_g_dl').beta)} months per g/dL, p=${fmt(term(mainModel, 'albumin_g_dl').p)}), higher CRP was adverse (${fmt(term(mainModel, 'crp_per_10').beta)} months per 10 mg/L, p=${fmt(term(mainModel, 'crp_per_10').p)}), and ECOG 2 versus 0 was strongly adverse (${fmt(term(mainModel, 'ecog_2').beta)} months, p=${fmt(term(mainModel, 'ecog_2').p)}).`);
