  lines.push('');
  lines.push(`Targeted therapy signals were biomarker-specific. Sotorasib had a positive adjusted main effect (${fmt(term(mainModel, 'treatment_sotorasib').beta)} months, p=${fmt(term(mainModel, 'treatment_sotorasib').p)}) and a strong positive interaction with kras_g12c (${fmt(iterations[6].analyses[0].effect_estimate)} months, p=${fmt(iterations[6].analyses[0].p_value)}). In kras_g12c-positive patients, sotorasib was associated with ${fmt(g8.diff)} longer PFS months (p=${fmt(g8.p)}), while the kras_g12c-negative comparison was small and not significant (${fmt(g9.diff)} months, p=${fmt(g9.p)}). Osimertinib similarly showed a positive main effect (${fmt(term(mainModel, 'treatment_osimertinib').beta)} months, p=${fmt(term(mainModel, 'treatment_osimertinib').p)}) and positive interaction with egfr_mutation (${fmt(iterations[10].analyses[0].effect_estimate)} months, p=${fmt(iterations[10].analyses[0].p_value)}). The egfr_mutation subgroup difference was ${fmt(g12.diff)} months (p=${fmt(g12.p)}), whereas the EGFR-negative comparison was not meaningful (${fmt(g25.diff)} months, p=${fmt(g25.p)}). Olaparib had a weaker but significant adjusted main effect (${fmt(term(mainModel, 'treatment_olaparib').beta)} months, p=${fmt(term(mainModel, 'treatment_olaparib').p)}) and a strong brca2_mutation interaction (${fmt(iterations[13].analyses[0].effect_estimate)} months, p=${fmt(iterations[13].analyses[0].p_value)}); in brca2_mutation-positive patients, olaparib was associated with ${fmt(g15.diff)} longer PFS months (p=${fmt(g15.p)}).`);
