+  lines.push(`Several plausible biomarker and treatment hypotheses were not supported. stk11_mutation was only weakly adverse (${fmt(finalStats.stk11.beta)} months, p=${fmt(finalStats.stk11.p)}), and brca2_mutation was independently adverse (${fmt(finalStats.brca2.beta)} months, p=${fmt(finalStats.brca2.p)}). However, pembrolizumab had no positive adjusted association (${fmt(finalStats.pembroMain.beta)} months, p=${fmt(finalStats.pembroMain.p)}), pdl1_tps had no meaningful main effect (${fmt(finalStats.pdl1.beta)} months per 0.50 higher value, p=${fmt(finalStats.pdl1.p)}), and the pembrolizumab by pdl1_tps interaction was null (${fmt(finalStats.pembroPdl1Interaction.beta)} months, p=${fmt(finalStats.pembroPdl1Interaction.p)}). Similarly, there was no evidence of biomarker-concordant benefit for osimertinib in egfr_mutation (${fmt(finalStats.osimertinibEgfrInteraction.beta)} interaction months, p=${fmt(finalStats.osimertinibEgfrInteraction.p)}) or olaparib in brca2_mutation (${fmt(finalStats.olaparibBrca2Interaction.beta)} interaction months, p=${fmt(finalStats.olaparibBrca2Interaction.p)}).`);
+  lines.push('');
+  lines.push('Overall, this cohort showed strong prognostic structure and one dominant predictive treatment interaction: sotorasib benefit was concentrated in KRAS G12C-positive disease. The evidence did not support the expected pembrolizumab-PD-L1, osimertinib-EGFR, or olaparib-BRCA2 benefit patterns in this dataset. The age and sex findings are notable because their directions are not the usual clinical expectation, so they should be treated as dataset-specific associations rather than causal conclusions.');
+
+  writeOutputs(transcript, lines.join('\n'));
+  console.log(`Wrote transcript.json and analysis_summary.txt with ${iterations.length} iterations.`);
+}
+
+main();

